      • getBaseDefinition

        public RuntimeResourceDefinition getBaseDefinition()
        If this definition refers to a class which extends another resource definition type, this method will return the definition of the topmost resource. For example, if this definition refers to MyPatient2, which extends MyPatient, which in turn extends Patient, this method will return the resource definition for Patient.

        If the definition has no parent, returns this
